    "body": "@spaceh3ad that means that the transaction reverted and there wasn't a reason string in the code. That is, you hit a:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nrequire(falseCondition)\r\n```\r\n\r\nstatement. That's not an error in Hardhat, it just means that you triggered a revert. You'll have to inspect the code of the involved contracts to figure out what happened. The stack trace at least gives you a hint: the revert happened in the contract at address `0x5aa53f03197e08c4851cad8c92c7922da5857e5d`.",
